{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.1","fallback":"Drizen: \"Guardian Gada, how extensive would you say our kingdom\'s historical record is?\"

Gada: \"I would describe it as fairly encompassing and highly accurate.\"

Drizen: \"And yet you say that we as Guardians have"}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.1","fallback":"no written record of the Ender peoples\' aid in the construction of our towers?\"

Gada: \"Correct. We know this to be true from their oral history--\"

Drizen: \"But is it not possible that they could be lying, or misrepresenting"}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.4","fallback":"merely when it occured. We simply don\'t recall how such a feat was achieved.\"

Drizen: \"But our ancestors could have done so themselves, without alien intervention?\"

Gada: \"I am not an architect.\""}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.5","fallback":"Drizen: \"In your opinion as an anthropologist?\"

Gada: \"...Anthropology often underestimates the skills and knowledge of ancient peoples and civilizations.\"

Drizen: \"Indeed. Moving on, you suggest that the Ender people may"}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.8","fallback":"might damage the other?\"

Gada: \"It is possible, but their culture suggests--\"

Gada: \"Putting aside whether they currently do or do not know the effects of their actions on the land might affect the sea,"}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.9","fallback":"is it possible that, whether by intent or ignorance, their warping of the Mystic Roughs could harm the aquatic ecosystem? We have all seen the purple water, after all.\"

Gada: \"We would know if this were the case.\"

Drizen: \"In the"}

{"translate":"nitdim.book.ancient.6.12","fallback":"Guardian, such as a King, could determine that these actions have or would become a threat if they continued. Is this hypothetical accurate?\"

Gada: \"As merely a hypothetical, yes.\"

Drizen: \"No further questions.\""}
